			<title><![CDATA[August '16 Release Thread]]></title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?78878-August-16-Release-Thread&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Mon, 01 Aug 2016 00:54:58 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[This is it, the moment everyone's been waiting for: the month when the last video game anyone will ever play finally comes out. 
 
I am, of course, jokingly referring to *No Man's Sky*, the space exploration sand box that people have been hyping themselves up for. I sort of expect that it's going...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>This is it, the moment everyone's been waiting for: the month when the last video game anyone will ever play finally comes out.<br />
<br />
I am, of course, jokingly referring to <b>No Man's Sky</b>, the space exploration sand box that people have been hyping themselves up for. I sort of expect that it's going to end up disappointing people. How could it not with the insane expectations and hype people are attaching to it? Still, it should be a neat game and be well worth checking out. <br />
<br />
<b>Deus Ex: Mankind Divided</b> is also a pretty big game set to release this month. The last game was great, and with a bigger budget I expect the next one to be even better. I forgot to mention it in the E3 thread, but one of the things they are adding to this game (raising a few eyebrows) is some kind of hacker heist multiplayer mode. While it wasn't needed, it sounds like they are at least trying something unique, and impressions from the main game still sound good.<br />
<br />
Not much on handhelds. 3DS is getting <b>Metroid Prime: Federation Force</b>, the game that angered fans that wanted a new &quot;real&quot; Metroid game focusing on exploration. This instead seems to be a multiplayer shooter with an added sports mode to the mix. Will be interesting to see how it is received on launch. I think in this case the branding hurt the product more than it helped it.<br />
<br />
Rounding out the month is a ton of smaller stuff, some of it I don't even recognize. The standouts (for me) are <b>Abzu</b>, an deep sea exploration game, and the start of the new <b>TellTale Batman</b> series.<br />
<br />
<b>Madden</b> and <b>World of Warcraft: Legion</b> are also due this month. The audience for these games probably doesn't need to be reminded of this.<br />
<br />
<br />
